WEBVTT

00:03.040 --> 00:04.210
Previously on
"A Million Little Things"...
I quit my job!

00:04.210 --> 00:06.040
What?
Yeah.

00:06.040 --> 00:07.250
Tom: Hey.
You're Maggie's friend.

00:07.250 --> 00:09.380
I'm Tom.
Gary.

00:09.380 --> 00:11.540
Grape soda.
How vintage.

00:11.540 --> 00:14.790
I thought I'd...drop off
a little care package.

00:14.790 --> 00:17.750
It can't be easy staring down
another round of treatment.

00:17.750 --> 00:19.210
Nope.

00:19.210 --> 00:20.960
Every day, you push away
more and more of Dad.

00:20.960 --> 00:22.920
I want to remember him.

00:22.920 --> 00:25.040
Why -- Why don't you?

00:25.040 --> 00:26.540
I don't know
where we go from here.

00:26.540 --> 00:28.670
I'm still trying to figure out
how we got here.

00:28.670 --> 00:30.460
I could blame it on
you and Delilah,

00:30.460 --> 00:31.460
but the truth is,

00:31.460 --> 00:32.540
we were broken
long before that.

00:32.540 --> 00:34.170
♪♪

00:35.920 --> 00:37.790
♪ My house in Budapest ♪

00:37.790 --> 00:39.000
♪ My hidden treasure chest ♪
Delilah: Hey, Gina.

00:39.000 --> 00:41.380
So, I got the, uh,
the tile samples,

00:41.380 --> 00:42.460
and I forgot --

00:42.460 --> 00:45.000
what did we say,
your place or mine?

00:45.000 --> 00:46.960
Everything okay, sweetie?

00:46.960 --> 00:48.750
[ Flatly ]
Yeah, Mom. Amazing.

00:48.750 --> 00:49.790
[ Door opens, slams ]

00:49.790 --> 00:51.460
My place it is.

00:51.460 --> 00:53.290
Oh, actually, uh, Rome,

00:53.290 --> 00:54.420
can D and I meet here,

00:54.420 --> 00:55.880
or do you
have to write today?

00:55.880 --> 00:57.460
Oh, no.
You're good.

00:57.460 --> 00:58.710
I got to run
an errand later anyway.
Great.

00:58.710 --> 01:00.250
[ Laughs ]

01:00.250 --> 01:01.460
She's 15.

01:01.460 --> 01:02.920
She'll be out of the house
in three years.

01:02.920 --> 01:04.080
Just stock up on wine.

01:04.080 --> 01:05.380
[ Cellphone beeps ]

01:05.380 --> 01:06.540
♪ Oh, for you ♪

01:06.540 --> 01:08.500
Gary: All right, sir,
let me ask you this.

01:08.500 --> 01:10.250
How many people
are actually gonna be with us

01:10.250 --> 01:11.250
on this thing?

01:11.250 --> 01:13.250
Because
between the two of us,

01:13.250 --> 01:15.670
the whole reason
I'm planning this trip

01:15.670 --> 01:17.330
is because
I'm trying to trick her

01:17.330 --> 01:19.120
into sharing
this pretty important secret

01:19.120 --> 01:20.960
she's been keeping from me.

01:20.960 --> 01:22.210
Oh, it's --

01:22.210 --> 01:23.420
You're the guy.

01:23.420 --> 01:24.540
It's -- It's us and you.

01:24.540 --> 01:26.000
Okay, um...
[ Dog barks ]

01:26.000 --> 01:27.750
...well, in that case, uh...

01:27.750 --> 01:28.880
Whoa. Whoa.

01:28.880 --> 01:30.750
Here she comes.
We'll see you soon.

01:30.750 --> 01:32.620
Just be cool.

01:32.620 --> 01:35.040
Okay, your Larry Bird Celtics
soap dispenser

01:35.040 --> 01:36.830
is officially
a cry for help.

01:36.830 --> 01:38.380
Please call my office.

01:38.380 --> 01:40.000
I will make you
a referral.

01:40.000 --> 01:42.000
And I'll have you know
that I painted

01:42.000 --> 01:43.750
that soap dispenser
all by myself

01:43.750 --> 01:45.880
when I took Theo
to Paint The Rainbow.

01:45.880 --> 01:46.710
Wow.
Mm-hmm.

01:46.710 --> 01:47.830
It's a masterpiece.

01:47.830 --> 01:49.620
You know
what Theo painted?
Hmm?

01:49.620 --> 01:51.170
An ashtray.

01:51.170 --> 01:52.750
Nobody smokes.

01:52.750 --> 01:54.040
Everybody
washes their hands.

01:54.040 --> 01:55.420
♪♪

01:55.420 --> 01:57.330
Go home, change,
pack a sweatshirt.

01:57.330 --> 01:58.250
No spoilers.

01:58.250 --> 02:00.040
And I will pick you up
at 11:00,

02:00.040 --> 02:03.460
and we will go
to an undisclosed location

02:03.460 --> 02:05.330
and share a day
that we will cherish

02:05.330 --> 02:07.080
for the rest of our lives.

02:07.080 --> 02:08.750
♪ And, baby, if you hold me,
then all of this will go away ♪

02:08.750 --> 02:10.540
Eddie: All right, buddy.
Here we go.

02:10.540 --> 02:11.670
Let's put it on.

02:11.670 --> 02:12.830
All right.

02:12.830 --> 02:15.710
All right, now, arms up.

02:15.710 --> 02:18.620
Your arms are branches.

02:18.620 --> 02:21.000
Katherine: No, Carter,
I'm e-mailing my redlines now.

02:21.000 --> 02:23.000
Have them inputted
before I get to court...
Oh!

02:23.000 --> 02:24.170
...so I can give them
to the judge.
Yeah!

02:24.170 --> 02:25.500
Theo: [ Chuckles ]
[ Phone beeps ]

02:25.500 --> 02:28.500
♪♪

02:28.500 --> 02:30.120
Oh, wow.

02:30.120 --> 02:32.330
This is great.

02:32.330 --> 02:34.460
It's really great.

02:34.460 --> 02:35.920
Eddie: Of course
it only took us,

02:35.920 --> 02:37.710
like, four trips
to Home Depot.

02:37.710 --> 02:39.670
Six.

02:39.670 --> 02:40.750
But it was worth it.

02:40.750 --> 02:44.040
Little man,
you're gonna be spectacular!

02:44.040 --> 02:45.620
It's just a small part.

02:45.620 --> 02:47.000
Small part?

02:47.000 --> 02:48.790
There are no small parts.

02:48.790 --> 02:50.750
Mommy's right.

02:50.750 --> 02:51.960
Ooh,
I have to get to court,

02:51.960 --> 02:53.750
but my whole office knows
that tomorrow morning,

02:53.750 --> 02:54.830
I will be going
to the theatre.

02:54.830 --> 02:56.830
But the show's today.

02:56.830 --> 02:59.330
No, it's the 8th.

03:01.170 --> 03:02.290
You told me
it was the 8th.

03:02.290 --> 03:04.670
[ Sighs ]

03:04.670 --> 03:06.380
It is today.

03:06.380 --> 03:08.210
It was moved because of
the field trip.
[ Sighs ]

03:08.210 --> 03:11.420
I thought they e-mailed
both of us.
No.

03:11.420 --> 03:14.380
Apparently they only e-mail
the primary parent.

03:14.380 --> 03:15.500
You're still coming,
right, Mommy?

03:15.500 --> 03:16.920
Hey,
you know what, bud?

03:16.920 --> 03:18.210
Why don't you

03:18.210 --> 03:19.920
go upstairs and put on
your school clothes?

03:19.920 --> 03:21.170
Theo: Okay.

03:22.620 --> 03:23.620
[ Exhales deeply ]

03:23.620 --> 03:26.460
[ Sighs ]

03:26.460 --> 03:28.290
Damn it.
I'm in court all morning.

03:28.290 --> 03:30.460
Listen.
It's gonna be okay.

03:30.460 --> 03:31.960
I can just film it.

03:31.960 --> 03:34.120
[ Exhales sharply ]

03:34.120 --> 03:37.250
You don't get it.

03:37.250 --> 03:38.920
I know you think
I'm distant.

03:38.920 --> 03:42.210
I am just...
trying to survive.

03:42.210 --> 03:44.170
I didn't get to see
our son awake yesterday.

03:44.170 --> 03:45.380
Well, no, we did FaceTime --

03:45.380 --> 03:46.670
Don't say "FaceTime"!

03:46.670 --> 03:48.620
Don't you dare say
"Face --"

03:48.620 --> 03:50.580
[ Inhales deeply ]
FaceTime was probably
invented by a woman

03:50.580 --> 03:54.830
who also didn't get to raise
the baby she had.

03:54.830 --> 03:57.170
I don't want
to go to court.

03:57.170 --> 04:00.170
I want to watch my son
be a tree.

04:00.170 --> 04:06.830
♪♪

04:06.830 --> 04:07.920
I was never
a difficult teenager.

04:07.920 --> 04:09.420
I was a delight.

04:09.420 --> 04:11.460
[ Laughs ]
My parents
were the crazy ones.

04:11.460 --> 04:13.170
Oh, my God.

04:13.170 --> 04:14.710
Well, I was the worst.

04:14.710 --> 04:16.040
Did you ever make
your mother cry?

04:16.040 --> 04:18.380
I made my father cry.

04:18.380 --> 04:20.620
I once backed his car
into his other car.

04:20.620 --> 04:22.080
[ Laughs ]

04:22.080 --> 04:25.120
[ Sighs ] Sophie's never
learning how to drive.

04:25.120 --> 04:26.080
It sounds like
you didn't either.

04:27.500 --> 04:28.830
[ Laughs ]

04:28.830 --> 04:32.120
I just -- I have so much
on my plate right now,

04:32.120 --> 04:34.080
and my plate
just got fuller.

04:34.080 --> 04:35.120
Just breathe.

04:35.120 --> 04:37.380
Everything
is gonna be okay.

04:37.380 --> 04:38.290
You're right.

04:38.290 --> 04:39.880
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

04:39.880 --> 04:41.210
Ugh.
Who is it?

04:41.210 --> 04:43.170
The principal
at Sophie's school.

04:43.170 --> 04:45.080
Hi, Mr. McIsaac.

04:45.080 --> 04:47.290
Oh, my goodness.

04:47.290 --> 04:48.920
Yeah, I-I'll be --
I'll be right there.

04:48.920 --> 04:50.040
Thank you.

04:50.040 --> 04:51.790
What happened?

04:51.790 --> 04:53.580
Sophie
just punched someone.
[ Gasps ]

04:53.580 --> 04:54.710
You sure
you don't want kids?

04:54.710 --> 04:55.830
I'm having a sale.

04:55.830 --> 04:57.830
Ooh,
I need to get down there.

04:57.830 --> 04:58.670
Do you want me
to drive you?

04:58.670 --> 05:01.380
I really don't.

05:01.380 --> 05:02.290
[ Door closes ]

05:02.290 --> 05:04.290
♪♪

05:08.710 --> 05:10.420
Eddie:
Guys, I messed up.

05:10.420 --> 05:12.420
"Snow White" starts
in under three hours,

05:12.420 --> 05:14.620
and I need to delay it
until Katherine gets there.

05:14.620 --> 05:15.790
Any ideas how?

05:15.790 --> 05:16.750
What do you got?
Throw them at me.

05:16.750 --> 05:18.120
Ooh! Ooh!

05:18.120 --> 05:20.500
You could just
pull the fire alarm.
That's on me.

05:20.500 --> 05:21.960
I should've been
more specific.

05:21.960 --> 05:23.120
No felonies.

05:23.120 --> 05:24.170
Well,
there goes my idea.

05:24.170 --> 05:25.330
I'm afraid to ask.

05:25.330 --> 05:26.540
Oh, you make
a real poison apple.

05:26.540 --> 05:28.170
Okay.

05:28.170 --> 05:30.330
That'll buy a couple hours,
or forever.
[ Laughs ]

05:30.330 --> 05:31.540
[ Water running ]
Come on, guys.
This is serious.

05:31.540 --> 05:32.880
What is that noise
I'm hearing?

05:32.880 --> 05:34.080
I'm making apple snacks

05:34.080 --> 05:35.500
for Theo's play,

05:35.500 --> 05:37.540
and I got lemon juice
in my fret finger.

05:37.540 --> 05:38.880
Fret finger?

05:38.880 --> 05:40.580
No, that's not a thing.

05:40.580 --> 05:41.880
[ Laughs ]

05:41.880 --> 05:44.080
Okay, guys, not helping.

05:44.080 --> 05:45.540
I need a win here.
Wait, wait.

05:45.540 --> 05:47.620
H-How -- How is this
your fault again?

05:47.620 --> 05:50.210
The whole reason Katherine's
not the primary parent

05:50.210 --> 05:52.460
is 'cause she's had
to work crazy hours

05:52.460 --> 05:54.210
ever since
my band imploded,

05:54.210 --> 05:56.000
and I don't know
if you guys are aware,

05:56.000 --> 05:58.420
but we're not
in a great place right now.

05:58.420 --> 06:00.210
Well, was that
before or after

06:00.210 --> 06:02.670
you slept with other members
of our friend group?

06:02.670 --> 06:05.250
Wow.
Yeah, I know.

06:05.250 --> 06:08.040
But Katherine has done nothing
but support me,

06:08.040 --> 06:09.540
and I want to support her.

06:09.540 --> 06:11.880
And you think getting her
to a second-grade play

06:11.880 --> 06:14.580
is gonna make up for years
of alcoholism and infidelity?

06:14.580 --> 06:16.330
You might want to check
your math on that.

06:16.330 --> 06:20.620
♪♪

06:20.620 --> 06:26.670
♪♪

06:26.670 --> 06:32.670
♪♪

06:32.670 --> 06:35.120
Are you ready to call
your first witness, counselor?

06:36.670 --> 06:38.540
Permission to approach,
Your Honor?

06:38.540 --> 06:46.540
♪♪

06:46.540 --> 06:49.040
Your Honor, I move to adjourn
until tomorrow morning.

06:49.040 --> 06:50.210
On what grounds,
counselor?

06:52.290 --> 06:54.290
Full disclosure,
Your Honor.

06:54.290 --> 06:55.790
My son is a tree
in the school play,

06:55.790 --> 06:57.250
and the forest takes the stage
at noon.

06:58.960 --> 07:01.500
No small parts.

07:01.500 --> 07:04.960
[ Chuckles softly ]
Exactly.

07:04.960 --> 07:06.880
Your Honor,
you know hard it is

07:06.880 --> 07:08.210
to be a working mother.

07:08.210 --> 07:10.210
Indeed.

07:10.210 --> 07:12.120
In fact, this morning,

07:12.120 --> 07:14.170
my daughter
had a fever of 102.

07:15.920 --> 07:18.460
And yet, here I am.

07:18.460 --> 07:20.710
Shall we call your
first witness, counselor?

07:20.710 --> 07:22.920
[ Chuckles ]

07:22.920 --> 07:26.420
♪♪

07:26.420 --> 07:28.540
And there's a part of me
that feels like

07:28.540 --> 07:31.380
I shouldn't be allowed
to tell them that I need help.

07:31.380 --> 07:32.790
I should be
stronger than that.

07:34.790 --> 07:37.000
'Cause you can't be the reason
you don't make it.

07:37.000 --> 07:38.420
What?

07:38.420 --> 07:40.250
That's how it works,
right?

07:40.250 --> 07:41.420
You can't be
the one in your family

07:41.420 --> 07:42.670
who's tapping out.

07:42.670 --> 07:44.080
It's hard enough.

07:44.080 --> 07:46.040
Between racism, gangs,

07:46.040 --> 07:47.420
police messing with us --

07:47.420 --> 07:50.880
you can't be the reason
you don't make it.

07:50.880 --> 07:52.080
Am I right?

07:53.830 --> 07:56.080
How am I supposed to
drive over here in my Tesla

07:56.080 --> 07:58.040
and tell you
that my life is bad?

07:58.040 --> 08:01.000
You have a right
to feel depressed, Rome.

08:01.000 --> 08:03.170
You have a right to acknowledge
that you're unhappy.

08:03.170 --> 08:04.460
But I can't.
And you have a right

08:04.460 --> 08:07.330
to be happy.

08:07.330 --> 08:08.540
[ Sighs ]

08:08.540 --> 08:12.540
♪♪

08:12.540 --> 08:14.540
I quit my job
to pursue my dreams.

08:14.540 --> 08:17.620
I thought
I'd feel different.

08:17.620 --> 08:20.330
But I don't.

08:20.330 --> 08:23.120
Is there a history of depression
in your family?

08:23.120 --> 08:24.120
There's a history of
"we don't talk about that"

08:24.120 --> 08:25.170
in my family.

08:25.170 --> 08:26.210
[ Chuckles softly ]

08:26.210 --> 08:28.000
No, my mom's a solid.

08:28.000 --> 08:29.380
My pops
is a real go-getter.

08:29.380 --> 08:31.080
Gets up at 4:30
every morning,

08:31.080 --> 08:32.380
works like
12 hours a day.

08:32.380 --> 08:34.000
He ain't got time
to be sad.

08:34.000 --> 08:36.830
Well, I think you should ask
your parents

08:36.830 --> 08:39.420
and keep talking to me,
if that helps.

08:39.420 --> 08:41.250
In the meantime,

08:41.250 --> 08:42.790
I am gonna start you
on an antidepressant.

08:44.540 --> 08:45.540
Really?

08:45.540 --> 08:47.120
Mm-hmm.

08:47.120 --> 08:49.460
Okay, so,
if I agree to do it,

08:49.460 --> 08:52.290
how long
do I have to take the meds?

08:52.290 --> 08:55.210
If they work,
for the rest of your life.

08:55.210 --> 09:01.830
♪♪

09:01.830 --> 09:04.250
Principal McIsaac:
As you know, at Holy Cross,

09:04.250 --> 09:06.460
we have
a zero-tolerance policy.

09:06.460 --> 09:09.380
But I'm also aware
that your family

09:09.380 --> 09:11.290
has been through a lot.

09:11.290 --> 09:12.540
Thank you for being
so understanding.

09:13.790 --> 09:17.120
It has been a difficult time
for us.

09:17.120 --> 09:20.580
Um, that said, Jon and I
never condoned violence,

09:20.580 --> 09:24.210
and I, for one,
am embarrassed, and...

09:24.210 --> 09:26.120
I'm sure, Sophie,
that you are, too.

09:28.920 --> 09:30.880
If I could,
I'd hit her again.

09:30.880 --> 09:32.380
Sophie,
I don't understand.

09:32.380 --> 09:35.290
Chloe didn't even touch you,
right?

09:35.290 --> 09:37.250
What makes you think
it'd be okay to hit her?

09:37.250 --> 09:39.790
She put Dad
on a prayer list,

09:39.790 --> 09:44.080
said suicide's a sin
and that he's burning in Hell.

09:44.080 --> 09:47.920
♪♪

09:52.880 --> 09:54.170
I know
that you're upset,

09:54.170 --> 09:56.880
and what Chloe did
was wrong.

09:56.880 --> 09:59.540
Look, I understand
that you're hurting --
Yeah, no.

09:59.540 --> 10:02.000
You don't understand,
and I don't expect you to.

10:02.000 --> 10:03.880
Whole reason
I go to Holy Cross

10:03.880 --> 10:05.460
is 'cause Dad went here.

10:05.460 --> 10:07.710
He took us to church,
he taught us to believe in God,

10:07.710 --> 10:08.790
and now the one person

10:08.790 --> 10:10.670
who understands how I'm feeling
is gone.

10:10.670 --> 10:12.080
I still think
that I understand --

10:12.080 --> 10:13.420
You know, the Bible says

10:13.420 --> 10:15.120
that you're not
supposed to take a life,

10:15.120 --> 10:16.380
but that's exactly
what God did,

10:16.380 --> 10:18.290
so either he doesn't exist
or he's a hypocrite.

10:18.290 --> 10:20.000
Which is it?
You can't believe that.

10:20.000 --> 10:21.620
God, are you kidding me?

10:21.620 --> 10:24.000
You don't believe in
any of this.

10:26.290 --> 10:29.290
You've been to church twice
in your entire life.

10:29.290 --> 10:31.210
Once when you married Dad,

10:31.210 --> 10:32.960
and then
when you buried him.

10:32.960 --> 10:36.290
♪♪

10:36.290 --> 10:38.880
So, Mr. Andrews,
am I to understand

10:38.880 --> 10:40.500
you were unaware
that Huntington Properties

10:40.500 --> 10:42.380
misrepresented their
second-quarter earnings?

10:42.380 --> 10:43.920
That's correct.

10:43.920 --> 10:47.120
You turned in your work laptop,
exhibit 22.

10:47.120 --> 10:49.620
Mr. Andrews,
did you delete

10:49.620 --> 10:50.960
any files
on the hard drive

10:50.960 --> 10:53.120
before surrendering
your laptop?

10:53.120 --> 10:54.460
Objection.
Speculative.

10:54.460 --> 10:56.210
He'll answer.

10:59.080 --> 11:00.790
It's possible.

11:00.790 --> 11:02.290
So, it's possible

11:02.290 --> 11:04.500
you deleted financial records
of a company

11:04.500 --> 11:05.750
prior to turning in

11:05.750 --> 11:08.000
a subpoenaed piece
of evidence?
Objection.

11:08.000 --> 11:09.830
Your Honor,
can we have the rest of the day

11:09.830 --> 11:11.080
to identify
any deleted files?

11:13.210 --> 11:14.920
Counselor?
I'm good with that.

11:14.920 --> 11:17.540
Court is adjourned
until 10:00 Monday morning.

11:18.330 --> 11:20.750
Well played, counselor.
Enjoy the theatre.

11:20.750 --> 11:22.460
Eddie: Perfect.

11:22.460 --> 11:25.290
Oh, cutest tree in the forest.
[ Laughs ]

11:25.290 --> 11:27.500
And thank you, Eddie,
for parking respectfully

11:27.500 --> 11:29.330
before getting
Theo's costume out.

11:29.330 --> 11:30.670
Unlike Kelly, who thinks

11:30.670 --> 11:32.330
just because she drove
three of the seven dwarves

11:32.330 --> 11:33.670
that she can hold up
the carpool lane

11:33.670 --> 11:34.920
for the better part
of 10 minutes.

11:34.920 --> 11:36.380
Hi, Gail.

11:36.380 --> 11:38.000
Hi. Come on.
Beth.

11:38.000 --> 11:39.330
Beth: Eddie.

11:39.330 --> 11:42.080
Hey, Dad.
Is Mom gonna be here?

11:44.080 --> 11:46.210
You know what, bud?

11:46.210 --> 11:47.790
She's gonna try her best.

11:47.790 --> 11:50.670
[ Sighs ]
"Try" always means "no."

11:50.670 --> 11:52.380
Child: Hey, Theo!

11:52.380 --> 11:57.960
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

11:57.960 --> 11:58.880
[ Cellphone beeps ]

11:58.880 --> 12:00.000
Hey, what's up?

12:00.000 --> 12:01.790
Hey, GPS has me there
in 38 minutes.

12:01.790 --> 12:03.250
Great.

12:03.250 --> 12:05.000
But the play
starts in 20.

12:05.000 --> 12:06.000
[ Sighs ]

12:06.000 --> 12:07.380
I'll stall.

12:07.380 --> 12:09.420
How are you gonna
do that?

12:09.420 --> 12:11.000
No idea.

12:11.000 --> 12:11.920
[ Exhales sharply ]

12:11.920 --> 12:15.920
♪♪

12:15.920 --> 12:17.250
Maggie: Wow!
Gary: Yep.

12:18.880 --> 12:22.790
I did not think of you
as a hot-air-balloon type.

12:22.790 --> 12:23.790
Well, drink it in.

12:23.790 --> 12:26.540
You know, Gary,
I got to say,

12:26.540 --> 12:27.790
I'm a little surprised.

12:27.790 --> 12:30.670
I'm a little
pleasantly surprised.

12:30.670 --> 12:32.960
Well, there's a lot
you don't know about me, Maggie.

12:32.960 --> 12:35.880
Maybe some things
I don't know about you.

12:35.880 --> 12:37.710
But I did check
this website.

12:37.710 --> 12:40.420
It looks great.

12:40.420 --> 12:42.420
The basket seemed bigger
online.
[ Chuckles ]

12:42.420 --> 12:43.880
Ooh!

12:43.880 --> 12:45.750
They're serving
chocolate-covered strawberries

12:45.750 --> 12:47.670
at 3,000 feet.

12:47.670 --> 12:49.960
3,000 feet?

12:49.960 --> 12:52.670
No, that's...got to be a typo,
right?

12:52.670 --> 12:55.460
♪♪

12:55.460 --> 12:57.000
Gail:
Okay, everybody, freeze.

12:57.000 --> 12:58.960
We are missing
the evil queen's apple.

12:58.960 --> 13:00.670
What?

13:00.670 --> 13:02.040
No red apple?

13:02.040 --> 13:04.080
There's no "Snow White"
without a red apple.

13:04.080 --> 13:05.540
Yeah,
that's what I just said.

13:05.540 --> 13:07.540
I will just
run to the store

13:07.540 --> 13:09.830
and, uh, be back
in like 20 minutes.

13:09.830 --> 13:11.540
Just go to
the teacher's lounge.

13:11.540 --> 13:12.460
There's like 40 in there.

13:12.460 --> 13:13.620
Okay, I got it.

13:13.620 --> 13:15.080
You're a hero.

13:16.540 --> 13:20.170
If you're interested
in continuing that streak,

13:20.170 --> 13:22.670
my wife is just running
a little late from work.

13:22.670 --> 13:25.330
Could you delay the production
20 minutes?

13:25.330 --> 13:27.500
Yeah...

13:27.500 --> 13:29.380
No.

13:29.380 --> 13:31.710
If we delay it,
the kids get hangry.

13:31.710 --> 13:35.460
But, you know,
the only reason

13:35.460 --> 13:37.040
she's running late
in the first place

13:37.040 --> 13:38.290
is because your school

13:38.290 --> 13:39.670
only e-mails
the primary parent.

13:39.670 --> 13:41.290
Well, Mr. Taylor,
in our family,

13:41.290 --> 13:42.540
we're both
the primary parent.

13:42.540 --> 13:43.750
I get it, Eddie,

13:43.750 --> 13:45.460
but a lot of parents here
have jobs to go back to.

13:45.460 --> 13:48.290
I promised Gail
we'd start the show by noon.

13:48.290 --> 13:50.120
[ Sighs ]
Okay, I get it.

13:50.120 --> 13:53.120
I mean,
Gail's a working mother, too.

13:53.120 --> 13:54.500
[ Gasps ]

13:54.500 --> 13:57.380
You know what?

13:57.380 --> 13:59.620
What happened with my wife
makes me realize

13:59.620 --> 14:02.540
it is about time
working mothers

14:02.540 --> 14:03.880
had more of a say
around here.

14:03.880 --> 14:06.000
Am I right, Gail?

14:06.000 --> 14:07.540
Gail: What's that?
I mean,
you're always telling me

14:07.540 --> 14:08.960
that the drop-off line
is inefficient

14:08.960 --> 14:10.290
and doesn't get her
back to work on time.

14:10.290 --> 14:11.620
Oh, yeah.

14:11.620 --> 14:13.330
If we're waiting for one kid
who forgot his backpack,

14:13.330 --> 14:15.210
the whole line
comes to a standstill.

14:15.210 --> 14:16.380
Two lanes --
it just makes sense.

14:16.380 --> 14:18.040
I thought we were talking
about the play.

14:18.040 --> 14:19.120
We're talking
about the play.

14:19.120 --> 14:20.210
We're talking
about pick-up.

14:20.210 --> 14:21.670
We're talking
about drop-offs.

14:21.670 --> 14:23.170
We're talking about
some kid's backpack.
It's everything...

14:23.170 --> 14:24.420
Yes.
...Taylor.

14:24.420 --> 14:26.460
Plus, I know
Beth has a few things

14:26.460 --> 14:28.000
to say about snacks.

14:28.000 --> 14:29.500
Beth:
Yes, I would like --
Gail: Beth, no.

14:29.500 --> 14:31.250
Okay, just 'cause
Lucas can't have sugar

14:31.250 --> 14:33.040
doesn't mean all the kids
have to suffer, okay?

14:33.040 --> 14:34.250
Gail: In the afternoon,
it needs to be safe

14:34.250 --> 14:35.460
for my second-grader
to come in.

14:35.460 --> 14:36.290
Beth: And we need more
after-school activities.

14:36.290 --> 14:37.380
Those fifth graders
start sooner --

14:37.380 --> 14:38.620
Swimming, drama classes.
I-I hear you.

14:38.620 --> 14:40.040
...'cause they're allowed
to walk together.

14:40.040 --> 14:41.380
A lot of things that
need to be done in this school.

14:41.380 --> 14:42.210
And maybe the buses
shouldn't line up in the front.

14:42.210 --> 14:43.500
And honestly,
you don't need --

14:43.500 --> 14:45.580
Renee: Walter, for once,
will you listen to me?

14:45.580 --> 14:47.500
Walter: I will as soon as
you make sense.

14:47.500 --> 14:49.210
Well, you need
to call someone.

14:49.210 --> 14:50.580
Someone costs money.
I'm free.

14:50.580 --> 14:52.170
Well, it won't be free

14:52.170 --> 14:54.210
when you fall off the ladder
and crack your skull open.

14:54.210 --> 14:56.210
I'm not moving
into no facility.

14:56.210 --> 14:57.540
I'm not gonna do it.

14:57.540 --> 14:58.580
Hey, Mom.

14:58.580 --> 15:00.460
Romie.

15:00.460 --> 15:03.120
[ Laughs ] I didn't know
you was dropping by.

15:03.120 --> 15:04.620
[ Laughs ]

15:04.620 --> 15:07.380
Maybe you can talk some sense
into your father.

15:07.380 --> 15:08.880
I'm not calling
a different man

15:08.880 --> 15:10.420
to fix something
in this man's house.

15:10.420 --> 15:12.040
Okay, Pop, you go ahead.
I got you.

15:12.040 --> 15:13.460
Two things --

15:13.460 --> 15:15.330
how much you pay
for those sneakers?

15:15.330 --> 15:16.540
And get your hands off
my damn ladder.

15:16.540 --> 15:18.040
[ Laughs ]

15:18.040 --> 15:19.170
Yeah.

15:19.170 --> 15:21.670
[ Door opens ]

15:21.670 --> 15:22.790
[ Keys jingle ]

15:22.790 --> 15:24.000
Delilah:
Sophie, you're suspended.

15:24.000 --> 15:24.880
I get it, Mom.

15:24.880 --> 15:25.960
It's on my permanent record,

15:25.960 --> 15:27.120
and I wrecked my life

15:27.120 --> 15:28.250
because I'm never
getting into Harvard.

15:28.250 --> 15:30.880
No, what I was gonna say
is you're suspended...

15:30.880 --> 15:32.210
I'm suspended.

15:32.210 --> 15:33.960
We're spending the day
together.

15:33.960 --> 15:36.000
What do you want to do?

15:38.000 --> 15:39.080
♪♪

15:39.080 --> 15:41.040
Gary: Okay.

15:41.040 --> 15:43.120
As we await
our inflatable

15:43.120 --> 15:44.460
and,
from the looks of it,

15:44.460 --> 15:47.460
highly combustible
chariot,

15:47.460 --> 15:52.500
sit back, relax,
and enjoy the fact

15:52.500 --> 15:56.000
that I have brought
the city of Chicago to you.

15:56.000 --> 15:57.580
Maggie: Oh, my God.

15:57.580 --> 15:59.250
[ Laughs ]
You hate deep dish.

15:59.250 --> 16:01.170
Because it's disgusting.
[ Laughs ]

16:01.170 --> 16:02.210
But if that is
the only way

16:02.210 --> 16:03.330
to score points
with Maggie Bloom,

16:03.330 --> 16:07.250
then I will eat this
soggy excuse for pizza.

16:07.250 --> 16:10.830
Note --
mushrooms on your half.

16:10.830 --> 16:13.420
What is happening?

16:13.420 --> 16:15.420
Just when I think
I know you, Gary.

16:15.420 --> 16:16.290
Well, that's what
today is all about.

16:16.290 --> 16:17.750
[ Exhales deeply ]

16:17.750 --> 16:19.460
Getting to know each other.

16:19.460 --> 16:22.750
Yeah, it's funny that
you say that, actually.

16:22.750 --> 16:23.750
Um...

16:25.620 --> 16:27.420
Um...

16:27.420 --> 16:31.290
I actually did want
to tell you something.

16:31.290 --> 16:35.080
You have
my undivided attention.

16:35.080 --> 16:37.250
Um...

16:37.250 --> 16:39.000
[ Soda can opens, hisses ]
Well...

16:39.000 --> 16:41.170
[ Sighs ]

16:43.790 --> 16:46.790
Mm, something's happened,
and --

16:46.790 --> 16:48.250
Is that grape soda?

16:48.250 --> 16:50.120
I love grape soda.

16:50.120 --> 16:51.920
It's delicious.
Please continue.

16:51.920 --> 16:53.750
We've never talked soda.

16:53.750 --> 16:55.290
How did you know?

16:55.290 --> 16:57.790
You know,
it's an easy leap to make.

16:57.790 --> 16:59.170
You drink a lot of wine.

17:01.250 --> 17:02.380
Tom.

17:02.380 --> 17:03.540
You talked to Tom.

17:03.540 --> 17:05.210
I don't know a Tom.

17:05.210 --> 17:07.040
I'm Gary
with the grape soda.

17:07.040 --> 17:09.330
[ Sighing ] My God.

17:09.330 --> 17:11.880
When he came by
with the care package.

17:11.880 --> 17:13.330
Of course.
Oh, my God.

17:13.330 --> 17:14.330
Okay, fine.

17:14.330 --> 17:15.830
The grape soda
was boring Tom's idea,

17:15.830 --> 17:16.830
but everything else is me.

17:16.830 --> 17:17.920
Okay, this whole day --

17:17.920 --> 17:19.460
Is a lie.

17:19.460 --> 17:22.000
Is this
this day of deception

17:22.000 --> 17:23.790
to try to get me
to open up to you?

17:23.790 --> 17:25.330
I mean, uh...

17:25.330 --> 17:27.290
What else
did he tell you?

17:30.250 --> 17:32.750
♪♪

17:32.750 --> 17:34.250
I am so sorry.

17:34.250 --> 17:35.750
I'm sorry.
I should've told you.

17:35.750 --> 17:37.580
I should've been
more straightforward.

17:37.580 --> 17:38.670
Okay, I know that.

17:38.670 --> 17:40.000
I blew it. I wanted to.

17:40.000 --> 17:42.830
I just -- I wanted you
to tell me yourself

17:42.830 --> 17:45.670
so that I could tell you
that I am here, okay?

17:45.670 --> 17:47.420
I am here,

17:47.420 --> 17:49.000
and I will do whatever it takes
to get you well,

17:49.000 --> 17:51.880
and we will fight this thing
together.

17:51.880 --> 17:54.080
[ Sighing ] Oh.
Okay?

17:56.380 --> 17:58.210
Look.

17:58.210 --> 18:00.500
[ Sighs ]

18:00.500 --> 18:04.580
The thing is that he didn't
tell you everything

18:04.580 --> 18:07.120
because he does not know
everything.

18:07.120 --> 18:09.080
What doesn't he know?

18:10.670 --> 18:13.040
I'm done with treatment.

18:13.040 --> 18:16.880
♪♪

18:16.880 --> 18:19.620
I'm not gonna fight
my cancer.

18:19.620 --> 18:23.120
♪♪

18:27.830 --> 18:29.880
[ Birds squawking ]

18:29.880 --> 18:33.750
♪♪

18:33.750 --> 18:36.080
Mmm! Wow.

18:36.080 --> 18:39.170
So, you're just gonna
let yourself die.

18:39.170 --> 18:41.250
I don't know
if you've heard, Gary,

18:41.250 --> 18:42.830
but we're all gonna die.

18:42.830 --> 18:44.710
The question is,

18:44.710 --> 18:46.040
what are you gonna do
with your life

18:46.040 --> 18:47.080
before that happens?

18:47.080 --> 18:49.080
I, myself,
am going to eat

18:49.080 --> 18:51.290
half of a mushroom
deep-dish pizza

18:51.290 --> 18:53.120
and take a romantic
hot-air-balloon ride.

18:53.120 --> 18:55.710
I encourage you
to join me.

18:55.710 --> 18:57.290
With all due respect,

18:57.290 --> 18:58.960
that's the stupidest thing
that your face has ever said.

18:58.960 --> 19:00.080
[ Chuckles ] Maybe.

19:02.790 --> 19:04.290
But I learned it
from you.

19:04.290 --> 19:06.420
What?

19:06.420 --> 19:07.750
The night we met --
In a remission group.

19:07.750 --> 19:10.000
Mm-hmm, exactly.

19:10.000 --> 19:14.040
I was not
supposed to be there,

19:14.040 --> 19:16.210
but I'm glad I was
because I met you.

19:16.210 --> 19:18.580
♪♪

19:18.580 --> 19:22.540
Do you know where I was
supposed to go the next day?

19:22.540 --> 19:23.540
Chemo.

19:23.540 --> 19:27.710
My first round...again.

19:27.710 --> 19:30.420
But instead,

19:30.420 --> 19:34.290
after hooking up
with a devilishly handsome guy,

19:34.290 --> 19:37.580
I went with him
to a funeral,

19:37.580 --> 19:40.580
and I met his crazy,
wonderful friends,

19:40.580 --> 19:42.880
who made me realize

19:42.880 --> 19:47.330
that I would rather keep
the life that I have right now

19:47.330 --> 19:50.040
than waste it
fighting for a future

19:50.040 --> 19:51.620
that I probably
won't even get.

19:51.620 --> 19:53.210
It doesn't have to be
that way!
Well, exactly.

19:53.210 --> 19:54.170
You of all people
should know that!

19:54.170 --> 19:55.380
No, I do know that.

19:55.380 --> 19:56.670
That's why
I'm not letting it.

19:58.880 --> 20:01.000
Gary, these last few weeks
have been better

20:01.000 --> 20:03.750
than the whole 28 years
before that.

20:03.750 --> 20:05.750
No way. I don't buy that.
No, you do the chemo, Maggie.

20:05.750 --> 20:06.790
You do the chemo,

20:06.790 --> 20:08.960
and then you get
28 more great years!

20:08.960 --> 20:09.710
You can't guarantee that,
Gary.

20:09.710 --> 20:10.670
You can't.

20:10.670 --> 20:12.040
No one can.

20:12.040 --> 20:14.500
But I can guarantee

20:14.500 --> 20:17.040
the quality of the time
that I have left.

20:17.040 --> 20:18.420
You're a numbers guy.

20:18.420 --> 20:20.710
You know
that I could fight this

20:20.710 --> 20:23.960
and have what the doctors say
is a 30% chance of living,

20:23.960 --> 20:26.250
or I could keep doing

20:26.250 --> 20:28.670
exactly what I'm doing
right now

20:28.670 --> 20:30.330
and have a 100% chance

20:30.330 --> 20:31.750
of loving the time
that I have left.

20:31.750 --> 20:33.790
♪♪

20:33.790 --> 20:34.830
[ Sighs ]

20:34.830 --> 20:38.420
♪♪

20:38.420 --> 20:40.540
Wow.

20:40.540 --> 20:41.830
[ Scoffs ]

20:41.830 --> 20:43.290
♪♪

20:43.290 --> 20:45.380
I -- I --

20:45.380 --> 20:46.920
I don't want you
to take this the wrong way,

20:46.920 --> 20:48.710
but I...

20:48.710 --> 20:50.540
really, really wish
you hadn't met me.

20:50.540 --> 20:55.670
♪♪

20:55.670 --> 21:01.040
♪♪

21:01.040 --> 21:03.710
Man: Got another one!

21:03.710 --> 21:06.040
Mom, it's back on!

21:09.880 --> 21:11.620
I thought
we were watching a movie.

21:11.620 --> 21:13.670
What -- What are you doing
with Doug?

21:15.080 --> 21:16.290
You still mad at Chloe?

21:16.290 --> 21:18.040
Yeah,
I hate her stupid face.

21:18.040 --> 21:20.380
Thought so.
That's why I brought up Doug.

21:20.380 --> 21:22.380
Let's put the gloves on.

21:27.120 --> 21:29.620
Dad bought all this equipment
and only used it once.

21:29.620 --> 21:30.830
[ Chuckles ]

21:30.830 --> 21:31.830
He burned more calories

21:31.830 --> 21:33.290
taking it
out of the packaging.

21:33.290 --> 21:34.380
[ Chuckles ]

21:34.380 --> 21:36.960
All right, let's
take it all out on Doug.

21:36.960 --> 21:39.790
Can I call him Chloe?

21:39.790 --> 21:41.540
[ Sighs ]
I don't think we should.

21:41.540 --> 21:43.460
[ Chuckles ]

21:44.500 --> 21:47.250
So, when are you
gonna put a baby in
that wife of yours?

21:47.250 --> 21:49.330
[ Chuckles ]
You know we ain't doing that.

21:49.330 --> 21:50.830
I just want you to have
what I have.

21:50.830 --> 21:52.920
[ Chuckles softly ]

21:54.920 --> 21:56.170
Dad.

21:56.170 --> 21:57.460
Mm-hmm?

22:00.540 --> 22:02.170
You ever feel, uh...

22:03.750 --> 22:05.920
You ever feel down...

22:05.920 --> 22:07.920
for more than
a couple of days?

22:07.920 --> 22:11.210
Maybe after
your grandma died.

22:13.880 --> 22:15.830
I'm not
talking about that.

22:17.750 --> 22:20.330
♪♪

22:20.330 --> 22:22.460
[ Ladder creaks ]

22:22.460 --> 22:26.040
Everybody feels sad, son.

22:26.040 --> 22:28.500
Feeling sad
is just a part of life.

22:28.500 --> 22:34.960
♪♪

22:34.960 --> 22:37.210
Gail: Oh, God.

22:37.210 --> 22:38.920
That was incredible.
Just incredible.

22:38.920 --> 22:40.920
I got so emotional.

22:40.920 --> 22:41.920
Oh, my God. I missed it.

22:41.920 --> 22:43.080
You didn't miss it.

22:43.080 --> 22:43.830
You didn't miss it.

22:43.830 --> 22:44.880
It starts in two minutes.

22:44.880 --> 22:46.620
What?
Yeah.

22:46.620 --> 22:49.250
Beth and, uh, Gail
started this whole thing

22:49.250 --> 22:51.120
with Mr. Taylor.
Oh.

22:51.120 --> 22:53.380
Your husband,
can I just tell you,

22:53.380 --> 22:55.000
he spoke up
for working moms,

22:55.000 --> 22:56.330
and for the first time,

22:56.330 --> 22:58.290
we're getting some results
around here.

23:00.210 --> 23:04.210
Yeah, I, uh, may have incited
a 20-minute debate

23:04.210 --> 23:06.830
about carpool lanes.

23:06.830 --> 23:08.750
For me?

23:10.250 --> 23:11.460
Uh, excuse me, guys?

23:11.460 --> 23:14.120
Uh, there's a problem
with Theo.

23:16.420 --> 23:18.500
Theo: Jenna says
I have a stupid part

23:18.500 --> 23:20.500
because I'm just a tree,

23:20.500 --> 23:22.460
and no one will even notice
if I'm up there or not.

23:22.460 --> 23:24.420
That is not true.

23:24.420 --> 23:26.580
She should know, Dad.
She's Snow White.

23:26.580 --> 23:28.210
You don't get it.

23:28.210 --> 23:31.120
When you were in your band,
you were the lead.

23:33.080 --> 23:36.000
Well,
I know how you feel.

23:36.000 --> 23:37.960
You know what's funny?

23:37.960 --> 23:41.120
Sometimes in the family,
I feel like that.

23:41.120 --> 23:42.710
You do?

23:42.710 --> 23:44.620
Sometimes.

23:44.620 --> 23:46.960
It's 'cause you and Dad
do such a great job

23:46.960 --> 23:48.290
of being the leads,

23:48.290 --> 23:52.420
but sometimes
'cause of work and stuff,

23:52.420 --> 23:55.580
I feel like just another tree
in the forest.

23:59.000 --> 24:00.750
You know what, buddy?

24:00.750 --> 24:04.040
Snow White can't get lost
in the forest...

24:05.790 --> 24:07.120
...without the forest.

24:07.120 --> 24:08.500
[ Giggles ]

24:08.500 --> 24:12.120
You know, sometimes
it's easy for us trees

24:12.120 --> 24:14.210
to forget how important
we really are.

24:16.120 --> 24:17.670
But it's nice
to be reminded.

24:19.670 --> 24:21.500
Isn't it?

24:21.500 --> 24:26.120
♪♪

24:26.120 --> 24:27.420
What's he doing?

24:27.420 --> 24:29.880
He wants you
to put his costume on him.

24:31.040 --> 24:32.580
Oh!

24:32.580 --> 24:35.460
♪♪

24:35.460 --> 24:36.540
Ready?
Yeah.

24:39.710 --> 24:41.540
Oh, my goodness.

24:41.540 --> 24:43.830
Mwah!

24:54.880 --> 24:56.920
[ Tires squeal ]

24:56.920 --> 24:58.080
Oh, for God's sake.

24:58.080 --> 24:59.250
Where are we going now?

25:01.460 --> 25:03.420
We are gonna
play basketball.

25:03.420 --> 25:05.920
Yeah, you want to live
in the moment?

25:05.920 --> 25:08.080
Play some basketball
in the moment.

25:09.380 --> 25:10.710
The game is to 21.

25:10.710 --> 25:12.170
Winner takes all.

25:12.170 --> 25:13.500
If I beat you,

25:13.500 --> 25:16.000
you're gonna fight cancer
with me by your side,

25:16.000 --> 25:19.960
and you're gonna win
just like you won last time.

25:19.960 --> 25:23.960
Unfortunately, right now,
you're gonna lose.

25:26.290 --> 25:27.580
Deal.

25:27.580 --> 25:30.880
But if I win,

25:30.880 --> 25:33.380
I am not
getting any treatment,

25:33.380 --> 25:36.880
and you can't so much
as mention it ever again

25:36.880 --> 25:39.380
to me or anyone.

25:39.380 --> 25:43.080
♪♪

25:43.080 --> 25:43.960
Game on.

25:43.960 --> 25:44.960
[ Trunk shuts ]

25:44.960 --> 25:47.500
♪♪

25:51.620 --> 25:52.830
Gary: Come on.
I'm waiting.

25:52.830 --> 25:53.670
Show me what you got.
I'm right here.

25:53.670 --> 25:55.040
Let's see. Huh?

25:55.040 --> 25:56.710
What are you waiting for?
[ Chuckles ]

25:56.710 --> 25:58.120
You want to retire
this jersey, Deep Dish?

25:58.120 --> 25:58.920
You're gonna
have to get by me.

25:58.920 --> 26:00.250
I will get by you

26:00.250 --> 26:02.210
and your wannabe
James Harden beard!

26:02.210 --> 26:04.040
Oh, no!

26:04.040 --> 26:05.710
Why would I go and do that?

26:05.710 --> 26:06.920
Not again!

26:06.920 --> 26:08.670
The beard must be...

26:08.670 --> 26:10.620
too tight.

26:10.620 --> 26:11.500
[ Chuckles ]

26:11.500 --> 26:12.580
6-1?

26:12.580 --> 26:14.290
6...1?

26:14.290 --> 26:16.080
1, yeah.

26:16.080 --> 26:18.750
You're gonna be spending
your golden years in Boca.

26:18.750 --> 26:20.500
[ Sighs ]

26:20.500 --> 26:23.000
Also, I think
we can probably ix-nay

26:23.000 --> 26:25.670
the full-court element.
Yeah. Yeah.

26:25.670 --> 26:26.830
What? Are you tired?

26:26.830 --> 26:29.040
What?
You tired?

26:29.040 --> 26:30.380
No, I just don't want
to be here all day, you know?

26:30.380 --> 26:31.120
Oh, okay.

26:41.080 --> 26:42.210
Ohh! Wow!

26:42.210 --> 26:43.250
Sophie:
[ Exhales deeply ]

26:43.250 --> 26:44.670
Nice.
You feel better?

26:44.670 --> 26:45.830
[ Panting ] No.

26:45.830 --> 26:48.790
Okay.

26:48.790 --> 26:50.500
Plan "B" --
let's eat our feelings.

26:50.500 --> 26:51.290
Yeah!

26:51.290 --> 26:52.710
Yeah.

26:52.710 --> 26:54.290
Sophie: Okay.

26:54.290 --> 26:55.540
♪♪

26:55.540 --> 26:57.710
I'm not gonna lie.

26:57.710 --> 27:00.040
I'm just --

27:00.040 --> 27:02.710
I'm a little bit worried

27:02.710 --> 27:03.750
about your ankles.

27:03.750 --> 27:04.250
Oh, come on.

27:05.880 --> 27:07.080
Great.

27:07.080 --> 27:11.210
15 for me.
6 for you.

27:11.210 --> 27:14.120
[ Singsong voice ]
We are going to chemo.

27:14.120 --> 27:16.750
We're going to chemo.

27:16.750 --> 27:17.750
[ Normal voice ]
What else you got?

27:17.750 --> 27:19.040
Huh, Hammer pants?

27:19.040 --> 27:20.580
Please, Hammer.

27:20.580 --> 27:21.670
Don't hurt 'em.
They're just --

27:23.670 --> 27:26.040
Maggie: You want to talk
about pants?

27:26.040 --> 27:28.460
You just got pantsed.

27:28.460 --> 27:30.000
Okay.

27:30.000 --> 27:31.750
So, you've got one move.

27:31.750 --> 27:34.380
That's gonna work
one time.

27:34.380 --> 27:38.250
Well, they did call me
"Magic Mags."

27:38.250 --> 27:40.120
Everybody thinks they're Magic
in grade school.

27:40.120 --> 27:41.290
Oh, no, this is college.

27:41.290 --> 27:43.710
Brown University,
Division I.

27:43.710 --> 27:44.790
Hold up.
Division I? No.

27:44.790 --> 27:47.540
You're 5-foot...child.

27:47.540 --> 27:48.540
[ Laughs mockingly ]

27:48.540 --> 27:49.960
Yes, I am,

27:49.960 --> 27:51.750
and that's what every
college recruiter used to say.

27:51.750 --> 27:54.170
And then I would...

27:54.170 --> 27:55.290
do this.

27:55.290 --> 27:58.790
♪♪

27:58.790 --> 28:00.330
That's bush league.

28:00.330 --> 28:02.080
You can't feel good
about that.

28:02.080 --> 28:03.920
It was all right.
Two can play at that game.

28:03.920 --> 28:06.830
♪♪

28:06.830 --> 28:08.920
Bye, Dad.

28:08.920 --> 28:10.750
Walter:
Thanks for the help, son.
Yes, sir.

28:10.750 --> 28:12.290
I love you, Mom.

28:12.290 --> 28:13.290
[ Chuckles ] Bye, baby.

28:13.290 --> 28:14.170
Bye.

28:16.790 --> 28:18.460
Listen.

28:18.460 --> 28:20.670
I heard you talking
to your father.

28:20.670 --> 28:22.790
Don't let him fool you.

28:22.790 --> 28:24.380
He's had his share
of dark days.

28:24.380 --> 28:25.170
Believe me.

28:27.000 --> 28:29.170
You've got
to take care of yourself.

28:29.170 --> 28:34.000
Not just for you,
but for Regina, too.

28:41.290 --> 28:42.710
[ Grunts ]

28:42.710 --> 28:43.710
Watch your ankles.

28:45.500 --> 28:48.000
[ Mockingly ]
Oh, no! 20-19.

28:48.000 --> 28:49.540
I guess
I'm keeping my eyebrows.

28:49.540 --> 28:51.170
[ Laughs ]

28:53.790 --> 28:56.120
[ Both sigh ]

28:59.380 --> 29:01.000
Maggie: Oh, my gosh.

29:01.000 --> 29:03.710
You are living to be 100.

29:03.710 --> 29:06.420
You're gonna be cruising
the applesauce aisle

29:06.420 --> 29:09.620
in a velour track suit
made for a baby.

29:09.620 --> 29:11.210
[ Sighs ]

29:11.210 --> 29:12.120
Next point wins.

29:12.120 --> 29:13.710
Next point wins.

29:16.290 --> 29:17.830
Uh-oh.

29:17.830 --> 29:19.580
Picked up your dribble.

29:19.580 --> 29:21.210
You'll never make this shot,
Deep Dish.

29:21.210 --> 29:26.710
♪♪

29:26.710 --> 29:28.620
Haha!

29:28.620 --> 29:29.670
I win!

29:31.540 --> 29:32.670
I win!

29:32.670 --> 29:35.920
[ Laughs ]

29:35.920 --> 29:39.210
[ Breathing heavily ]

29:39.210 --> 29:40.830
It's not fair.
You hustled me.

29:40.830 --> 29:41.960
You know you did.

29:41.960 --> 29:45.170
Cancer's not fair.

29:45.170 --> 29:46.750
[ Breathing heavily ]

29:46.750 --> 29:49.380
Okay.

29:49.380 --> 29:50.830
Nice game.

29:50.830 --> 29:52.620
Well played, Ms. Bloom.

29:52.620 --> 29:55.420
♪♪

29:55.420 --> 29:57.040
Have it your way.

29:57.040 --> 30:00.290
♪♪

30:04.620 --> 30:06.210
All right,
we've done chicken wings,

30:06.210 --> 30:07.710
nachos,
movie-theater candy.

30:07.710 --> 30:09.080
What's next?

30:09.080 --> 30:11.120
How about
you take me to school

30:11.120 --> 30:13.120
so I can throw up
on Chloe?

30:13.120 --> 30:16.460
[ Chuckles ]

30:16.460 --> 30:18.960
You know,
Chloe doesn't know where Dad is.

30:18.960 --> 30:20.120
I don't know
where Dad is.

30:20.120 --> 30:21.580
I wish he was here

30:21.580 --> 30:24.250
because I think he'd have
all the answers for us.

30:25.580 --> 30:27.330
And I don't know
if there's a Heaven or a Hell,

30:27.330 --> 30:29.460
but if there is,

30:29.460 --> 30:31.290
I would love to believe
that he's in Heaven

30:31.290 --> 30:34.500
'cause I just refuse to believe
that he's in Hell.

30:34.500 --> 30:37.210
[ Sighs ]

30:37.210 --> 30:40.210
I just have
all these questions

30:40.210 --> 30:42.790
and hardly enough answers.

30:42.790 --> 30:44.290
You're 15.

30:44.290 --> 30:46.880
You're not supposed
to have these questions yet.

30:46.880 --> 30:48.170
I'm 43.

30:48.170 --> 30:49.790
I'm still trying
to figure it all out.

30:50.960 --> 30:53.170
Really?

30:53.170 --> 30:54.710
Yes.

30:54.710 --> 30:57.960
It's like that song goes,
remember?

30:57.960 --> 31:00.080
"Someday you'll find it."

31:00.080 --> 31:02.580
"Rainbow Connection."

31:02.580 --> 31:06.080
Your dad sang that to you
right through my belly.

31:06.080 --> 31:07.540
Yeah, I came out thinking

31:07.540 --> 31:08.750
my dad
was Kermit the Frog.

31:08.750 --> 31:10.420
[ Laughs ]

31:10.420 --> 31:14.120
Maybe Kermit's trying
to tell us something.

31:14.120 --> 31:15.750
Hmm?

31:15.750 --> 31:18.000
Someday we'll find it.

31:18.000 --> 31:20.460
Maybe not today,
maybe not tomorrow,

31:20.460 --> 31:24.250
but I'm gonna be
right here with you

31:24.250 --> 31:26.710
until you find all the answers
you're looking for.

31:29.380 --> 31:30.330
Thanks, Mom.

31:32.330 --> 31:35.120
And when you find them,
share them with me.

31:35.120 --> 31:37.960
And from now on,
only hit Doug.

31:37.960 --> 31:39.460
Deal. [ Chuckles ]

31:44.420 --> 31:46.580
And you're going
to Harvard

31:46.580 --> 31:47.880
and I'm coming with you.

31:47.880 --> 31:48.880
Oh.
Kidding.

31:48.880 --> 31:50.880
[ Laughs ]
Okay.

31:50.880 --> 31:52.170
[ Water running ]

31:52.170 --> 31:54.170
Hey, buddy.
Brush your teeth!

31:54.170 --> 31:56.750
Then you get 15 minutes
of screen time.

31:56.750 --> 31:59.120
All right,
I'm gonna smell your breath.

31:59.120 --> 32:00.120
I'm not.

32:00.120 --> 32:01.580
[ Both chuckle ]

32:01.580 --> 32:04.750
[ Dishes clatter ]

32:04.750 --> 32:06.670
Man,
he was so great today.

32:06.670 --> 32:08.830
I can't stop thinking
about, uh,

32:08.830 --> 32:10.040
the curtain call.
[ Water stops ]

32:10.040 --> 32:11.460
[ Laughs ]

32:11.460 --> 32:12.830
He started bowing
and he never stopped.

32:12.830 --> 32:14.960
I wanted to yell
"Timber!"

32:14.960 --> 32:16.250
[ Both laugh ]

32:16.250 --> 32:17.880
On the plus side,

32:17.880 --> 32:20.120
his costume was all padding,
so he was fine.

32:20.120 --> 32:22.330
[ Both laugh ]

32:22.330 --> 32:24.040
[ Sniffs ]

32:24.040 --> 32:26.330
[ Sighs ]

32:26.330 --> 32:27.580
Thanks for today.

32:27.580 --> 32:34.710
♪♪

32:34.710 --> 32:37.500
I wanted you to see your son
be a tree.

32:37.500 --> 32:46.830
♪♪

32:46.830 --> 32:49.380
I can't be with you
anymore.

32:49.380 --> 32:54.830
♪♪

32:54.830 --> 32:56.710
We worked well together
today,

32:56.710 --> 32:59.040
and it reminded me
of what we don't have.

32:59.040 --> 33:01.290
This isn't us.

33:04.500 --> 33:06.540
Maybe it can be.

33:06.540 --> 33:07.790
We were great today.

33:07.790 --> 33:09.540
Yeah, but instead of
making me happy,

33:09.540 --> 33:14.420
it made me angry
about everything.

33:14.420 --> 33:17.330
I don't think
I can get past it,

33:17.330 --> 33:20.170
and I don't think
I should have to.

33:20.170 --> 33:23.670
I don't know
if I believe in us anymore.

33:23.670 --> 33:29.540
♪♪

33:29.540 --> 33:31.540
I spent so much time
trying to figure out

33:31.540 --> 33:35.170
why you've done
the things you've done,

33:35.170 --> 33:37.580
and I realized
what I need to figure out

33:37.580 --> 33:40.830
is why don't I feel like
I deserve more.

33:40.830 --> 33:47.040
♪♪

33:47.040 --> 33:48.790
[ Seafret's "Give Me Something"
plays ]

33:48.790 --> 33:54.210
♪♪

33:54.210 --> 33:59.620
♪♪

33:59.620 --> 34:02.460
So, tomorrow night,

34:02.460 --> 34:04.960
you want to go check out
that new taco place

34:04.960 --> 34:06.620
in Coolidge Corner?

34:06.620 --> 34:09.210
You're asking me
if I want to eat tacos?

34:09.210 --> 34:11.460
Of course
I want to eat tacos.
[ Chuckles ]

34:11.460 --> 34:14.710
Okay, well, I finish with
my last patient at 6:00, so...

34:14.710 --> 34:15.830
6:01 it is.

34:15.830 --> 34:16.960
Okay.

34:16.960 --> 34:17.960
[ Seatbelt clicks ]

34:17.960 --> 34:21.290
♪♪

34:21.290 --> 34:24.170
♪ Take me down a road ♪

34:24.170 --> 34:26.620
♪ I believe in ♪

34:26.620 --> 34:27.920
♪♪

34:27.920 --> 34:30.670
♪ Lost the way ♪

34:30.670 --> 34:35.250
I can't --
I can't do this.

34:35.250 --> 34:38.420
I ca--
I can't watch you die.

34:38.420 --> 34:41.790
♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh, ooh-ooh ♪

34:41.790 --> 34:42.960
Okay.

34:42.960 --> 34:44.790
Please, please.

34:44.790 --> 34:48.170
Please don't ask me to.

34:48.170 --> 34:51.670
Please ask me to stay.

34:51.670 --> 34:53.460
Look, I'm --
Look, I'm right --

34:53.460 --> 34:54.540
I'm right here,

34:54.540 --> 34:56.170
and we'll fight this
together.

34:56.170 --> 34:59.330
And we will beat this...
together.

34:59.330 --> 35:02.290
[ Voice breaking ]
That's not the deal.

35:02.290 --> 35:04.620
♪ No reflection ♪

35:04.620 --> 35:07.040
♪♪

35:07.040 --> 35:08.920
♪ Take me to a place ♪

35:08.920 --> 35:10.540
Wait, don't do it.

35:10.540 --> 35:12.460
Don't go.
Don't. Don't. Don't.

35:12.460 --> 35:13.460
♪ I believe in ♪
Don't get out of the car.

35:13.460 --> 35:15.000
Don't. Don't. I --

35:15.000 --> 35:16.580
♪ Lost my way ♪
Don't get
out of the car.

35:16.580 --> 35:18.670
♪♪

35:18.670 --> 35:20.710
♪ Lost all reason ♪
[ Sniffles ]

35:20.710 --> 35:23.120
♪♪

35:23.120 --> 35:26.960
♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh ♪

35:26.960 --> 35:29.500
♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh, ooh-ooh ♪

35:29.500 --> 35:30.420
♪ Give me something ♪

35:30.420 --> 35:32.710
Thank you
for a great day.

35:32.710 --> 35:34.540
♪ Give me something ♪
[ Sighs ]

35:34.540 --> 35:35.670
Bye, Gary.

35:35.670 --> 35:36.790
[ Door closes ]

35:36.790 --> 35:38.580
♪ Give me something ♪

35:39.960 --> 35:42.000
♪ To hold on to ♪

35:43.920 --> 35:45.830
♪ I've got nothing ♪

35:47.080 --> 35:49.000
♪ Since I lost you ♪

35:49.000 --> 35:51.290
Eddie:
You guys have been saying
for months now

35:51.290 --> 35:53.540
that Katherine and I
should split.

35:53.540 --> 35:55.460
You finally
got what you wanted.

35:55.460 --> 35:58.960
Gary: Come on, Ed,
that's not what we wanted.

35:58.960 --> 36:00.830
What we wanted was
for you to be happy.

36:00.830 --> 36:02.080
Yeah.

36:02.080 --> 36:03.580
And you weren't.
Remember?

36:03.580 --> 36:06.620
[ Whistle blows
on television ]

36:06.620 --> 36:09.540
I don't know
what I'm gonna do.

36:09.540 --> 36:13.670
[ Man speaks indistinctly
on television ]

36:13.670 --> 36:16.500
[ Sighing ] Okay.

36:16.500 --> 36:18.460
My couch is your couch.

36:18.460 --> 36:20.790
As long as you need it.

36:20.790 --> 36:22.210
Rome: [ Chuckles ]

36:25.040 --> 36:28.620
Thanks, roomie.

36:28.620 --> 36:30.380
Maggie's gonna love that.
Oh, yeah.

36:30.380 --> 36:31.170
Who doesn't love dating
an adult man

36:31.170 --> 36:32.120
with a roommate?

36:32.120 --> 36:33.620
[ Chuckles ]

36:33.620 --> 36:35.830
[ Man speaking indistinctly
on television ]

36:35.830 --> 36:37.460
Yeah, my life isn't going

36:37.460 --> 36:39.290
exactly the way I want it to
right now.

36:39.290 --> 36:42.000
Announcer:
Get an icing call.

36:42.000 --> 36:44.080
When we come back...
Then we're gonna
get along great.

36:44.080 --> 36:45.580
...2:12 left in the second.

36:45.580 --> 36:47.040
[ Theme music plays ]
Commercial break.

36:47.040 --> 36:48.000
Bathroom break!

36:48.000 --> 36:50.290
Gary: I'm --
I called it!

36:50.290 --> 36:51.670
This is exactly why --
I called it!

36:51.670 --> 36:53.540
This is why
you're getting the couch, Ed.

36:53.540 --> 36:54.580
[ Door opens, closes ]

36:54.580 --> 36:55.750
I'll go to the master.

36:55.750 --> 36:57.290
Stay out of
Regina's cosmetics,

36:57.290 --> 36:58.540
and for the last time,

36:58.540 --> 37:00.120
cocoa butter
is not a food.

37:02.540 --> 37:04.380
[ Sniffs ]

37:04.380 --> 37:06.120
[ Exhales sharply ]

37:06.120 --> 37:07.580
[ Sniffs ]

37:07.580 --> 37:14.710
♪♪

37:14.710 --> 37:16.830
Uh, Rome?

37:16.830 --> 37:18.540
No, no, no, no.

37:18.540 --> 37:20.040
Gary:
Okay, okay. Relax.

37:20.040 --> 37:21.420
This is just a box.

37:21.420 --> 37:22.620
No!
It doesn't mean
that she's --

37:22.620 --> 37:24.120
Don't even say the word.

37:24.120 --> 37:25.080
Well, that's not how
you get someone pregnant.

37:25.080 --> 37:26.620
You should know that.

37:26.620 --> 37:28.540
Guys, let's look at the stick.
Where is the stick?

37:29.540 --> 37:31.170
There it is.
Eddie: Oof.

37:31.170 --> 37:33.620
How are you so nonchalantly

37:33.620 --> 37:35.960
touching the part of the stick
Regina urinated on?

37:35.960 --> 37:37.290
[ Pregnancy test clatters ]

37:37.290 --> 37:38.750
Come on.

37:38.750 --> 37:40.330
Why would sh--
Why would she do that?

37:40.330 --> 37:41.960
Well, don't smell it.

37:41.960 --> 37:43.290
How does a man

37:43.290 --> 37:44.880
who's had as much
promiscuous sex as you

37:44.880 --> 37:46.500
not know
how a pregnancy test works?

37:50.040 --> 37:51.210
Congratulations, Papa.

37:51.210 --> 37:53.330
Dude. Dude.

37:53.330 --> 37:55.330
q[ Laughs ]
I just quit my job.

37:55.330 --> 37:57.670
I -- Oh, man.

37:57.670 --> 37:59.290
[ Laughs ]

37:59.290 --> 38:01.080
Gina and I said no kids.

38:02.790 --> 38:04.040
I just quit my job.

38:04.040 --> 38:05.620
I just quit it.

38:05.620 --> 38:06.750
♪♪

38:06.750 --> 38:07.960
Listen to me.

38:07.960 --> 38:09.420
[ Exhales deeply ]

38:09.420 --> 38:11.460
My life sucks.

38:11.460 --> 38:15.000
I'm gonna be sleeping
on Gary's couch.

38:15.000 --> 38:16.250
I don't even get
the guest room.

38:16.250 --> 38:18.380
What is this speech?
Okay.

38:18.380 --> 38:21.420
Even though everything
is so bad for me right now,

38:21.420 --> 38:23.120
I wouldn't change a thing

38:23.120 --> 38:25.880
because if I did anything
differently,

38:25.880 --> 38:27.920
I wouldn't have Theo.

38:27.920 --> 38:30.540
♪♪

38:30.540 --> 38:36.880
And he is the greatest thing
I've done ever,

38:36.880 --> 38:38.380
and this baby might be

38:38.380 --> 38:40.790
the best thing
you've ever done.

38:40.790 --> 38:42.710
[ Chuckles ]

38:42.710 --> 38:44.290
Come on, man.

38:44.290 --> 38:45.670
[ Faucet turns on ]
The best thing
I've ever done

38:45.670 --> 38:47.170
is wash my hands.

38:50.670 --> 38:52.210
[ Guitar plays ]

38:52.210 --> 38:55.080
♪ Why are there so many ♪

38:55.080 --> 38:58.380
♪ Songs about rainbows? ♪

38:58.380 --> 39:00.790
[ As Kermit the Frog ]
♪ And what's on
the other side? ♪

39:00.790 --> 39:04.750
